{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}

How about expanding the eye-space with 1?
Sometimes it is good, but now it is a \cf1\b greedy\cf0\b0  move. White plays the vital point at 2 and captures Black immediately.

Even if Black connects at 3, White destroys the eye with 4 and Black can't live anymore.


