Well, then how about Black 1?
This is one of the 1-2 points. Is it good enough for Black to live?

White plays the placement at 2, if Black would play another move, he would live with this one.
Therefore \cf1\b 2 is the vital point\cf0\b0 .

The idea of playing the vital point at the 1-2 point was good but the \cf2\b direction\cf0\b0  was a \cf2\b bit strange\cf0\b0 .
